        "subject": "LU-19296 docs: improve lfs-changelog.1 formatting",
        "message": "LU-19296 docs: improve lfs-changelog.1 formatting\n\nImprove the lfs-changelog.1 man page formatting and\norganization:\n\n- Fix synopsis to use proper single-line option format\n  with escaped hyphens and proper spacing\n- Add dedicated OPTIONS section following man page\n  standards\n- Improve DESCRIPTION section flow and remove .TP\n  formatting for command descriptions\n- Split long command example across lines for better\n  readability\n- Use consistent punctuation in examples (e.g.,)\n- Remove duplicate text about changelog registration\n\nThese changes improve readability and follow standard\nman page conventions while maintaining all functionality\nfrom the original LU-19296 patch.\n\nTest-Parameters: trivial\nSigned-off-by: Patrick Farrell <pfarrell@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: Ie8690bf891b850bebf637fd06343fbfad91691c7\n"
